h8UwZHN5hKU0d_kVGmz35upvj8W5H5nZvRMA ) whether this heralded a shift in bus=
iness model. A few pertinent points from that Article:

* First, I recounted the Android-iPhone wars, and how Google made a mistake=
 in prioritizing features for Android instead of retaining its privileged p=
osition on the iPhone; the latter was important because Google is a service=
s company that ought to be reaching the most people possible.
* Second, I noted the Assistant business model problem: simply giving an an=
swer didn=E2=80=99t leave room for Google=E2=80=99s auction-based business =
model; this is obviously a concern that hasn=E2=80=99t gone away with the r=
ise of AI ( https://stratechery.com/2023/ai-and-the-big-five/?access_token=
=3DeyJhbGciOiJSUzI1NiIsImtpZCI6InN0cmF0ZWNoZXJ5LnBhc3Nwb3J0Lm9ubGluZSIsInR5=
